The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes a defence mechanism based on the second Kerckhoffs's cryptographic principle. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as these categories are closely related to the topics discussed in the paper.
